\chapter{Introduction}

Spanish West Africa (Spanish: África Occidental Española) is a former possession in the western Sahara Desert that Spain ruled after giving much of its former northwestern African possessions to Morocco. It was created in December 1946, and combined [Ifni](../ifni/Inroduction), [Cape Juby](../cape-juby/Introduction) and [Spanish Sahara](../spanish-sahara/Introduction).

